'''Opera软件'''（{{lang-no|'''Opera Software AS'''}}），成立於1995年，源自[[挪威|挪威]]最大的[[电信|电信]]公司[[Telenor|Telenor]]於1994年的研究项目，是由[[谭咏文|譚詠文]]和[[盖尔·伊瓦尔绥|盖尔·伊瓦尔绥]]創立。

Opera的總部位於挪威[[奧斯陸|奧斯陸]]，並在[[歐洲|歐洲]]、[[中國|中國]]和[[非洲|非洲]]設有辦事處<ref>{{Cite web|date=2016-09-12|title=A Tour of Opera Software’s Super Cool Wroclaw Office|url=https://www.officelovin.com/2016/09/12/tour-opera-softwares-super-cool-wroclaw-office/|access-date=2020-10-30|website=Officelovin'|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210130192615/https://www.officelovin.com/2016/09/12/tour-opera-softwares-super-cool-wroclaw-office/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Chan|first=Isabelle|title=Opera sets up office in India|url=https://www.zdnet.com/article/opera-sets-up-office-in-india/|access-date=2020-10-30|website=ZDNet|language=en|archive-date=2020-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200810074937/https://www.zdnet.com/article/opera-sets-up-office-in-india/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Street|first=Kenyan Wall|title=Opera Software opens Kenya & Nigeria offices, pumps $100M to grow African digital economy|url=https://www.african-markets.com/en/news/africa/opera-software-opens-kenya-nigeria-offices-pumps-100m-to-grow-african-digital-economy|access-date=2020-10-30|website=african markets|language=en-gb|archive-date=2021-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128181642/https://www.african-markets.com/en/news/africa/opera-software-opens-kenya-nigeria-offices-pumps-100m-to-grow-african-digital-economy|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2018年7月27日，Opera軟件在[[那斯達克|那斯達克]]證券交易所上市，[[首次公開發行|首次公開發行]]融資約1.15億美元<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/opera-browser-raises-115-million-in-initial-public-offering/|title=Opera browser raises $115 million in initial public offering|last=Shankland|first=Stephen|date=July 27, 2018|work=[[CNET|CNET]]|access-date=July 27, 2018|archive-date=2021-01-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210105151332/https://www.cnet.com/news/opera-browser-raises-115-million-in-initial-public-offering/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 历史 ==
Opera軟件由[[谭咏文|譚詠文]]和[[盖尔·伊瓦尔绥|盖尔·伊瓦尔绥]]於1995年在挪威成立，是一家獨立公司<ref name="milestones">{{cite web|url=http://www.opera.com/company/about/milestones/|title=About Opera - Opera|website=Opera.com|access-date=30 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081011064244/http://www.opera.com./company/about/milestones/|archive-date=2008-10-11|url-status=dead|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他們最初在挪威電信公司[[Telenor|Telenor]]工作時就開始開發Opera網頁瀏覽器<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/opinion/qna/opera-is-the-oldest-browser-and-it-is-still-surviving-jon-tetzchner-founder-opera-software/articleshow/7068303.cms|access-date=2020-09-17|title=存档副本|archive-date=2020-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201023080324/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/opinion/qna/opera-is-the-oldest-browser-and-it-is-still-surviving-jon-tetzchner-founder-opera-software/articleshow/7068303.cms|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

Opera軟件的第一款產品[[Microsoft_Windows|Windows]]的Opera網頁瀏覽器2.10版本於1996年公開發布。Opera於1998年開始開發第一款用於移動設備平台瀏覽器<ref name="milestones" />。

1996年，Opera瀏覽器最初為[[共享軟體#試用軟件或試用版軟件（Trialware、Demo_Software、Trial_Software、Demoware）|試用軟件]]，必須在試用期結束後購買，直到在2000年5.0版本發布之後，Opera轉型為廣告贊助商，在沒有經過同意的情況下向使用者展示廣告而受到批評。隨著8.5版本（2005年發布）的發布，廣告被完全移除，主要的財務支援轉由來自谷歌（Opera的預設搜尋引擎）的收入<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.theregister.com/2000/12/06/opera_browser_goes_free/ |title=Opera browser goes free with version 5.0 launch |last=Lettice |first=John |publisher=The Register |date=6 December 2000 |accessdate=11 October 2007 |archive-date=2012-05-29 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120529/http://www.theregister.com/2000/12/06/opera_browser_goes_free/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Baker">{{cite news |url=http://www.searchenginejournal.com/opera-goes-free-with-help-from-google/2227/ |title=Opera Goes Free with Help from Google |last=Baker |first=Loren |publisher=Search Engine Journal |date=20 September 2005 |accessdate=12 October 2007 |archive-date=2011-01-28 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5w4B9XAE7?url=http://www.searchenginejournal.com/opera-goes-free-with-help-from-google/2227/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2004年，Opera軟件與一家「國際公司」達成和解，並向Opera軟件賠償了1275萬美元。據猜測，宣布和解的聲明中提到的「國際公司」是[[微軟|微軟]]，微軟之前曾讓Opera使用者無法正常瀏覽MSN.com網站<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/microsoft-behind-12-million-payment-to-opera/|title=Microsoft behind $12 million payment to Opera|last=Hansen|first=Evan|date=May 24, 2004|work=|newspaper=CNET|access-date=October 25, 2016|via=|archive-date=2018-05-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180504011537/https://www.cnet.com/news/microsoft-behind-12-million-payment-to-opera/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/opera-wails-about-msn-problem/|title=Opera wails about MSN problem|last=Hansen|first=Evan|date=May 24, 2004|work=|newspaper=CNET|access-date=October 25, 2016|via=|archive-date=2018-03-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180306202350/https://www.cnet.com/news/opera-wails-about-msn-problem/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2007年，Opera軟件指控微軟將[[Internet_Explorer|IE]]捆綁到Windows上銷售，[[欧洲联盟委员会|歐盟]]對此展開調查後宣佈，微軟這一做法造成了對瀏覽器市場的壟斷，這項控訴導致建立[[BrowserChoice.eu|BrowserChoice.eu]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.zdnet.com/article/opera-files-complaint-against-microsoft-in-the-eu-over-ie-windows-bundle-cto-makes-web-standards-case/ |title=Opera files complaint against Microsoft in the EU over IE, Windows bundle; CTO makes Web standards case |last=Dignan |first=Larry |publisher=[[ZDNet|ZDNet]] |date=13 December 2007 |access-date=17 June 2020 |archive-date=2020-08-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801130301/https://www.zdnet.com/article/opera-files-complaint-against-microsoft-in-the-eu-over-ie-windows-bundle-cto-makes-web-standards-case/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://arstechnica.com/microsoft/news/2009/12/microsoft-to-randomly-generate-browser-ballot-list.ars |title=Microsoft to randomly generate EU browser ballot list |publisher=Ars Technica |access-date=14 November 2010 |archive-date=2012-05-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120508080517/http://arstechnica.com/microsoft/news/2009/12/microsoft-to-randomly-generate-browser-ballot-list.ars |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2013年，Opera軟件決定不再使用自行開發的桌面瀏覽器渲染引擎。從第15版本開始，桌面上的Opera瀏覽器將使用[[Blink|Blink]]渲染引擎，這是一個與谷歌一起開發的WebKit的分支<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gsma.com/newsroom/press-release/winners-2015-global-mobile-awards/|title=GSMA ANNOUNCES WINNERS OF THE 2015 GLOBAL MOBILE AWARDS|accessdate=4 March 2015|archive-date=2018-05-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180514005750/https://www.gsma.com/newsroom/press-release/winners-2015-global-mobile-awards/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2015年9月，Opera推出了全新品牌的品牌標識，並且從最初的Opera Software改名為Opera<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?t=8&v=KvJJk5Z-iZE Revealing the new Opera brand] {{Wayback|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?t=8&v=KvJJk5Z-iZE |date=20190217115129 }}. Opera, on YouTube. 21 September 2015. Retrieved 2018-01-04.</ref>。

2016年2月10日，一個來自中國的團體向Opera提出了1.2億美元（每股8.31美元）的收購邀約，<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/11/business/dealbook/china-opera-kunlun-qihoo-golden-brick.html|title=Chinese Group Bids $1.2 Billion for Company Behind Opera Web Browser|last=Tsang|first=Amie|date=2016-02-10|last2=Mozur|first2=Paul|newspaper=The New York Times|accessdate=2017-01-13|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2017-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170709105926/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/11/business/dealbook/china-opera-kunlun-qihoo-golden-brick.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>但據說未獲監管部門批准。<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.engadget.com/2016/07/18/opera-browser-sold-to-a-chinese-consortium-for-600-million/|title=Opera browser sold to a Chinese consortium for $600 million|accessdate=2017-01-13|work=Engadget|archive-date=2017-01-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119051639/https://www.engadget.com/2016/07/18/opera-browser-sold-to-a-chinese-consortium-for-600-million/|dead-url=no}}</ref>2016年7月18日，Opera宣布其已經出售[[Opera電腦瀏覽器|旗下瀏覽器]]、隱私及性能應用程式業務予金磚資本管理有限公司（一個包括[[奇虎360|奇虎360]]和崑崙萬維在內的中國投資者財團），據報收購金額為6億美元。<ref name=":0" />該筆出售Opera消費者級業務的交易在2016年10月31日獲得美國外國投資委員會批准。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/idUSASN0003I4|title=BRIEF-Opera Software says wins approval for China sale|date=2016-10-31|newspaper=Reuters|accessdate=2017-01-13|archive-date=2016-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104001803/http://www.reuters.com/article/idUSASN0003I4|dead-url=no}}</ref>2016年11月4日，金磚資本管理有限公司完成了該筆收購。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newsweb.no/newsweb/search.do?messageId=412755|title=NewsWeb|accessdate=2017-01-13|work=www.newsweb.no|archive-date=2017-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170129214654/http://www.newsweb.no/newsweb/search.do?messageId=412755|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.goldenbrickcapital.com/Portfolio.html|title=金砖资本管理有限公司|accessdate=2017-01-13|work=www.goldenbrickcapital.com|archive-date=2017-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116145235/http://www.goldenbrickcapital.com/Portfolio.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2017年12月18日，其母公司Opera Software ASA在出售其瀏覽器業務後更名為[[Otello_Corporation|Otello Corporation]]<ref>{{cite web|author1=Opera Software ASA|title=Minutes Extraordinary General Meeting|url=http://www.newsweb.no/newsweb/search.do?messageId=440989&siteLanguage=en|publisher=Oslo stock exchange|accessdate=18 December 2017|date=18 December 2017|archive-date=2018-01-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180105011548/http://www.newsweb.no/newsweb/search.do?messageId=440989&siteLanguage=en|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Oslo-listed Opera Software ASA changes name to Otello Corporation|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-opera-software-namechange-otello/oslo-listed-opera-software-asa-changes-name-to-otello-corporation-idUKKBN1EC11H|publisher=Reuters|accessdate=4 January 2018|date=18 December 2017|archive-date=2019-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825030836/https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-opera-software-namechange-otello/oslo-listed-opera-software-asa-changes-name-to-otello-corporation-idUKKBN1EC11H|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2021年1月20号，Opera软件宣布{{Internal link helper/en|YoYo Games|YoYo Games}}被其收购，并将成立Opera游戏部门<ref>{{Cite web|title=YoYo Games, the company behind GameMaker, is now part of Opera|url=https://blogs.opera.com/news/2021/01/opera-yoyo-games-gamemaker/|accessdate=2021-01-21|author=Opera Team|date=2021-01-20|format=|publisher=Opera Software|language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120140419/https://blogs.opera.com/news/2021/01/opera-yoyo-games-gamemaker/|archivedate=2021-01-20|dead-url=no}}</ref>。据{{Internal link helper/en|GameDaily|GameDaily}}报道，此次收购金额为1000万[[美元|美元]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=Opera acquires PlayTech's YoYo Games for $10m|url=https://gamedaily.biz/article/1959/opera-acquires-playtechs-yoyo-games-for-10m|accessdate=2021-01-21|author=Aiden Strawhun|date=2021-01-20|format=|publisher=gamedaily.biz|language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210121065302/https://gamedaily.biz/article/1959/opera-acquires-playtechs-yoyo-games-for-10m|archivedate=2021-01-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

